text: Tshering Tobgay (born 19 September 1965) is a Bhutanese politician who is serving as the Prime Minister of Bhutan since 2024, he served as Prime Minister previously from 2013 to 2018. He began his term as Prime Minister in 2012. His predecessor was Jigme Thinley. ==References== Category:1965 births Category:Prime ministers of Bhutan Category:Living people Category:Bhutanese politicians Category:Current national leaders
